         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en" source="#jmr-jbwp-rgg2003">
            <p>There will be a curse from the Father the Son, and the Holy Spirit
               if anyone were to bury a stranger here.</p></div>
            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en" source="#edd">
            <p>There will be a curse from the Father the Son, and the Holy Spirit
               if anyone buries a stranger here.</p></div></div>
         
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p><!-- line 1: On this spelling cf. Ch. Michel, s.v anatheme, Cabrol-Leclercq I, col. 1926. -->
               line 3: The form of the curse is paralleled on a tomb-stone from Beer-Sheba, dated in C.E.588,
               SEG 34.1469 (<bibl><title>PHI</title> <citedRange n="PH320108">320108</citedRange></bibl>)</p>
         </div>
         
